# Render CLI Preflight

Before running ANY `render` CLI command, read `~/.render/cli.yaml` and verify:

1. **`workspace`** field exists and is non-empty
2. **`api.key`** field exists and is non-empty
3. **`api.expires_at`** is a Unix timestamp in the future (compare against current time via `date +%s`)

If any check fails, STOP and tell the user:
- If workspace is missing: "Run `render workspace set` in your terminal to select a workspace."
- If api.key is missing or expires_at is in the past: "Run `render login` in your terminal to re-authenticate, then `render workspace set`."

Do NOT attempt any `render` CLI command until all three checks pass.

## Config file location
`~/.render/cli.yaml`

## Expected structure
```yaml
version: 1
workspace: <workspace-id>
workspace_name: <workspace-name>
api:
  key: <api-key>
  expires_at: <unix-timestamp>
  host: https://api.render.com/v1/
  refreshtoken: <refresh-token>
dashboard_url: https://dashboard.render.com
```
